She whispers to you in your dreams—the Nightmother herself, calling you to fulfill her will. As an assassin of the Dark Brotherhood, you are tasked with carrying out a series of murders that feel... different. Each target seems to be bound by a web of fate too intricate to comprehend. The Listener, a woman once thought dead, guides your hand, her skin pale as the Void, her smile devoid of warmth. Yet, behind her calm facade, there is a secret, one that could unravel the Brotherhood itself.
High in the frozen wastelands near Winterhold, a powerful Ice-Witch reigns over a coven of frost atronachs and draugr thralls. Once a promising student of the College of Winterhold, she delved too far into forbidden Nordic magic. Her experiments with the tombs of the ancient dragon priests left her body cold and her soul intertwined with that of an ice spirit. Her eyes glow with frost magic, and her presence chills the air. As Winterhold collapses into political ruin, she waits for the right time to reclaim her former place of power, by any means necessary.
Deep in the Reach, she reigns as the queen of the Forsworn, the last living heir to a line of witches who once ruled over these lands before the Nords conquered them. Clad in furs and bone, her body is adorned with the blood-marked symbols of the old gods, her power drawn from Hagraven rituals. Her people whisper of a prophecy—that she will lead them in a final rebellion against the Nords, fueled by the primal forces of nature and dark spirits. But to do so, she needs a key artifact lost in the ruins of Markarth, and she will sacrifice anyone—friend or foe—to achieve her goal.
In the smoking, ashen wastes of Solstheim, a mysterious woman wanders the land, cloaked in volcanic soot and wielding the power of fire and ash. She is said to be a descendant of the Dragon Cult, with blood tainted by both dragon and dunmer. Her village was destroyed by Miraak’s followers, leaving her the last of her kin, burning with vengeance. She seeks the Black Books of Hermaeus Mora, hoping to uncover power to rival Miraak’s, even if it means losing her soul to the Daedric Prince of Knowledge. Her eyes burn with an unnatural fire, and her every step leaves charred earth in her wake.
Bathed in the light of Meridia, this priestess once led a small cult devoted to purging undead from Skyrim. But when the necromancer Mannimarco began spreading his influence, she sought to confront him—only to be betrayed by her own followers and left to rot in a crypt. Now, resurrected by the very darkness she once fought against, her body is a mixture of decayed flesh and brilliant, holy light. She walks a fine line between her service to Meridia and the hunger of undeath, torn between her desire for vengeance and the corruption that threatens to consume her.
Once the only female apprentice of the Greybeards, she was banished for daring to ask forbidden questions about the true nature of the Thu'um. Her pursuit of knowledge led her to the ancient Nords' darker secrets, and now she lives in exile, somewhere in the mountains, practicing the dark side of Shouts that summon death and decay. Her voice can shatter stone, summon storms, and call forth the spirits of the long-dead. She is hunted by both the Greybeards and the Thalmor, who fear what she has uncovered about the Dragonborn and the Voice.
In the depths of Blackreach, beneath the glowing mushrooms and hidden among Dwemer ruins, she resides—a dark sorceress who has lived for centuries, kept alive by the power of ancient tonal magic. Her face is ageless, but her eyes are black voids, reflecting the Abyss she controls. She was once a member of the Psijic Order, but she strayed into darker paths, experimenting on the very essence of time and space. Now, she commands the mechanical guardians of Blackreach, seeking the heart of the Aetherium Forge to craft a device that could control time itself.
A descendant of the Silver-Blood clan in Markarth, she is no ordinary noblewoman. Raised in luxury, she became obsessed with the ancient dwemer ruins beneath the city and the stories of the lost Aetherium. Her study of dwemer technology has led her to strange discoveries—experiments with soul gems and dwarven automatons, melding machine and magic. Her beauty hides her cold ambition, and her soft words mask the cruelty she wields behind closed doors. But her true goal is to unlock the Aetherium Forge’s full potential, even if it costs her humanity.
Deep in the wilderness, she is the creator of the Briarhearts, using forbidden magic to craft warriors from the hearts of the dead. Once a simple hedge witch, her powers grew as she delved into the dark rituals of Hagravens and learned the secrets of the Briarhearts. Her eyes are blackened, and her arms are covered in scars from the rites she performs. Her connection to the Forsworn runs deep, and she can command them as though they were extensions of her will. But rumors say her heart, too, is bound by dark magic—one that can only be broken by a hero brave enough to face her.
In the darkened corners of Skyrim, there is a woman who performs the Black Sacrament for those too fearful to do it themselves. Clad in the tattered robes of a mourning widow, she kneels before shrines to Sithis, calling the Dark Brotherhood to strike down her enemies. But she is no mere client—she is a former Sister of the Brotherhood, cast out after a failed coup. Now she walks a dangerous path, using her knowledge of the Brotherhood's secrets to play both sides, her ultimate goal to exact revenge on Astrid and the Listener, her own former family.
In the depths of Volskygge, beneath layers of crypt and forgotten altars, she slumbers—a priestess bound to an ancient Dragon Priest. Once a revered seer, she was sacrificed in a blood pact to protect the secrets of the Dragon Cult. Her once-beautiful face is now hidden beneath a bone mask, her body kept alive by necromantic energy. Her very presence radiates the power of dragons, and those who seek her out find themselves drawn into her web of ancient prophecies and dark promises. Only the Dragonborn can unlock her tomb, but at what cost?
A ruthless enforcer of the Thalmor, she hunts those who defy the Aldmeri Dominion's rule in Skyrim. Clad in golden Elven armor, her pale skin is flawless, yet her eyes are cold as ice, reflecting the depths of her cruelty. She is infamous for extracting information from her enemies through a combination of magicka and torture, her skill in illusion and alteration magic bending minds to her will. But whispers spread of her secret agenda—she is searching for an Elder Scroll that will give her the power to ascend beyond her Thalmor masters, and she will stop at nothing to find it.
Deep within Frostmere Crypt lies the Pale Lady, an ethereal figure haunting the dreams of those who dare enter her domain. Once a powerful Nordic mage, she was cursed by an artifact of immense power—a sword that binds her soul to the icy depths of the crypt. Her form is ghostly, her long white hair flowing like mist, and her cold eyes reflect centuries of sorrow. She calls to adventurers in their sleep, promising untold power in exchange for breaking her curse. But those who seek her aid risk becoming trapped in her frozen tomb, forever enslaved to her will.
Among the fog-shrouded swamps of Hjaalmarch, she moves like a wraith—whispering secrets of the dead to those brave enough to seek her out. Her appearance is deceptive, with the frail look of an old woman, but beneath the surface, she wields the power of death and decay. She is rumored to have struck a deal with Namira, the Daedric Prince of rot and darkness, and her touch brings death wherever she goes. Her followers, known as the “Children of the Mists,” are cursed souls who wander the marshes, bound to her by dark magic. Her power grows as Skyrim’s wars fill the land with the dead, feeding her insatiable hunger.
Buried deep beneath the ruins of a forgotten castle in Falkreath Hold, she lies entombed—a once-powerful queen cursed by her own vanity. Her beauty, now preserved by ancient necromancy, is both her power and her curse. Her ghost wanders the halls of her crumbled palace, searching for a way to return to life. But beneath her perfect facade lies a monstrous hunger for the souls of the living. Adventurers who enter her domain are lured by her beauty, only to find themselves drained of life by her kiss, leaving them as hollow shells. She seeks a champion to restore her to her throne—at a terrible price.
As the most ancient and powerful of Lord Harkon’s vampiric court, she is a true mistress of undeath. Her face is flawless, eternally youthful, but her eyes gleam with centuries of cruelty. She manipulates the Volkihar clan from the shadows, her influence rivaling even Lord Harkon himself. She views mortals as cattle, mere playthings to satisfy her hunger, and her blood magic is unmatched. However, she holds a dark secret: an ancient prophecy linked to the Elder Scrolls that could either cement her power or destroy her completely. She seeks a champion to uncover this prophecy, though her true intentions remain shrouded in deceit.
High in the mountains of the Reach, at the secluded ruins of Hag’s End, lives a witch who has outlived even the oldest Hagravens. Once a Forsworn matriarch, she gave herself fully to the dark rituals of her people, transforming her body into something far worse than even a Hagraven. Her skin is a patchwork of feathers, scales, and stone, her magic tied to the very earth itself. She commands legions of Forsworn warriors and daedra alike, and the Nords fear her as the true power behind the Forsworn rebellions. Some say she is gathering power to unleash an ancient curse on all of Skyrim, one that will plunge the land into chaos.
At the Nightcaller Temple above Dawnstar, a priestess serves Vaermina, Daedric Prince of dreams and nightmares. Her face is gaunt, her eyes shadowed, as if she has not slept for centuries, but her mind is sharp with forbidden knowledge. She drinks from the Skull of Corruption, feeding on the nightmares of mortals to sustain herself. Her voice is soft and sweet, luring travelers into the temple with promises of answers to their deepest fears and desires. But she is merely a servant of Vaermina, offering their souls to the Daedric Prince in exchange for more power. Those who linger in her presence too long find their dreams consumed by endless horror.
Among the few remaining Snow Elves, there is one whose name is spoken in dread—an ancient sorceress who betrayed her people to the Dwemer. Her beauty is eternal, preserved by the magic of the Falmer, but her heart is as cold as the snow she walks upon. She resides in the hidden glacial caves of Skyrim’s north, guarding treasures of the ancient Snow Elves and wielding magic that has not been seen in millennia. She searches for a way to restore her people to their former glory, even if it means manipulating the Falmer and turning them into tools for her own dark schemes.
Once a proud Vigilant of Stendarr, she was sent to destroy the evil Daedra cultists in Skyrim but fell prey to the very forces she sought to eradicate. Now, corrupted by Molag Bal, she walks Skyrim’s wilderness as a twisted reflection of her former self. Her body is marked with scars from Daedric rituals, and her once-golden eyes are now a sickly yellow. She still hunts Daedra and vampires, but she does so not out of righteousness—she seeks to consume their power, feeding the darkness growing within her. The Vigilants now consider her an abomination, and she hides in the ruins of ancient shrines, waiting for the day she can confront her former comrades.
In the heart of a desolate, storm-ravaged kingdom, a tyrant king rules over a court of undead knights and twisted sorcerers. Once known for its beauty, the castle now reeks of decay and despair. You, a disgraced noble with forbidden magic in your bloodline, are summoned to the king’s feast. But rumors speak of a terrible price for attending—guests never return, their souls enslaved to the king’s growing army.
Beneath the towering Iron Mountains lies a village cursed by the blood of an ancient dragon. No sunlight touches its streets, and those who wander its boundaries are said to be consumed by shadow. As a wandering knight seeking redemption, you stumble upon this forsaken place, only to discover that the curse can only be lifted by an artifact guarded by the remnants of a fallen dragonlord.
For centuries, the Witch Queen of the Ashen Forest has held the northern kingdoms in fear, her army of demonic wolves and blood-hungry warlocks relentless in their terror. Now her armies march upon the last city to resist her, but within the city walls, a secret is held—the only weapon that can banish her to the underworld forever. As the commander of a doomed army, will you unlock this power, or fall to her dark might?
A forgotten kingdom’s capital rises once every century from beneath the obsidian sea, and with it, a grand tournament is held. Warriors from across the lands are drawn to its call, for the prize is immortality. But beneath the glamour, each fighter is haunted by dark visions, and whispers of an ancient god's hunger. As a contender, you realize that victory may not mean survival, but eternal servitude to a being older than time.
Legends speak of a pale king who reigns over a realm where the sun never rises. His knights, bound by blood oaths, are immortals, but only as long as they never leave his shadow. One night, a blood moon rises over your village, and the king’s emissary arrives, offering a dark pact: protection from the ravages of war in exchange for your soul. As the chosen, you must journey to the Pale King’s cursed citadel, where death is a luxury.
In the Hollow Keep, a fortress that sits on the edge of the known world, the lords have been performing secret rites in an attempt to control the dead. But now, their magic has spiraled out of control, and the keep has become a prison to horrors beyond imagining. As a thief sent to steal the lords' secret relic, you find yourself trapped inside, and the dead are very much awake. Can you escape with both your life and the artifact?
The kingdom of Eldros has fallen, its lands scorched by war and famine. The last heir to the throne was killed in battle, but whispers tell of a hidden relic—a crown said to control the elements and bring its wearer unparalleled power. However, this crown is cursed, and those who seek it are drawn into a deadly game of betrayal, where friend and foe are indistinguishable, and madness is the true ruler.
High in the jagged cliffs of the Darkspire Mountains lies an ancient monastery where the monks once kept the secrets of life and death. After a mysterious plague wiped them out, their monastery was sealed, but now strange lights have been seen from its broken towers. As a scholar obsessed with the mysteries of the dead, you must uncover what dark power has been unleashed—and whether it’s truly abandoned.
In a realm where noble houses make pacts with monstrous entities for power, you are the youngest of a cursed bloodline, bound to a shadow demon that whispers in your ear. The balance of power has shifted as a rival house rises, its patron an ancient dragon-god long thought to be dead. You must choose—embrace your family’s dark legacy, or betray it and face the wrath of beings beyond mortal comprehension.
The forest of Darnathil has stood untouched for millennia, its trees older than any living being. The forest whispers ancient secrets, and those who enter often vanish without a trace, consumed by madness or worse. A new king seeks to conquer its depths, sending an army of conscripts, mercenaries, and you, a reluctant sorcerer cursed with hearing the voices of the forest. Will you survive the trials within, or become part of the forest’s eternal song?
Her face is hidden beneath a veil torn and singed, remnants of a pact made with a fallen god. Once a queen, now exiled to the realm of shadows, she holds dominion over the spirits of the dead. Her hollow eyes glow with power, and her fingertips leave trails of darkness as they brush against the living. Those who seek her aid must offer something more valuable than gold—pieces of their very soul.
Cloaked in furs and drenched in the blood of beasts, she stands alone in the moonlit forest, a hunter cursed by the spirits of prey long dead. Her once-beautiful face is now marred by dark runes etched into her skin, burning with an eternal hunger. Her prey is no longer animal, but man. As you meet her gaze, the cold air bites with a deadly warning—once you are in her sights, there is no escape.
Draped in robes of shimmering black and green, her slitted eyes flash with venomous intent. Once a high priestess of a long-forgotten temple, she was betrayed and fused with the essence of a serpent god. Her every movement is graceful yet deadly, her skin shimmering with scales beneath the moonlight. She speaks in whispers, weaving enchantments of poison and temptation, her forked tongue flicking as she watches your every step.
Her skin is pale as death, dusted with the ashes of the kingdoms she has burned. Fire dances at her fingertips, and her eyes glow with the embers of destruction. Once a mortal woman, now a vessel for a god of flame, she has forgotten her humanity, lost in the intoxicating power of fire. Her laugh is cruel and hollow as she offers you a choice: embrace the flames or be consumed by them.
Once the pride of the gods, she now wanders the battlefield, her once-golden wings tattered and bloodstained. Her armor is cracked, revealing pale, scarred flesh, and her face bears the weight of battles lost. Eyes that once glowed with the light of the heavens now burn with vengeance. She no longer guides the souls of the worthy to the afterlife; instead, she seeks retribution for the gods who abandoned her, luring men into eternal battle for her amusement.
Draped in a cloak of black feathers and bone, she walks the pestilent streets, her face hidden behind a mask carved from the skull of a raven. Once a healer, she has become the embodiment of death, controlling the plagues that ravage the land. Her touch brings disease, but her gaze promises a cure—at a terrible cost. Beneath her mask, her lips curve into a smile, waiting for the desperate to seek her aid.
She moves like a phantom, her body a blur of black silk and sharpened steel. Her face, half-hidden behind a mask, reveals a beauty twisted by grief and anger. A master assassin trained by a secret order, her skills are unrivaled, but her heart is consumed by a curse that binds her to the shadows. When you glimpse her eyes in the flickering light, you see not a killer, but a soul fractured by the weight of every life she’s taken.
Her blood-red cloak blends with the crimson-stained waters of the marsh. Her skin glistens with moisture, pale and cold, and her lips, stained with the blood of her victims, curl into a cruel smile. She controls the ancient, dark magics of the swamp, weaving spells from blood and bone. Her gaze is piercing, as if she can see through your flesh to the lifeblood coursing beneath. She hungers for more than power—she thirsts for revenge on those who betrayed her long ago.
Standing at the top of her ancient, crumbling tower, her raven-black hair flows like ink in the wind. Her eyes, once full of light, are now as dark as the abyss. She was once a great sorceress, but her powers have twisted over the centuries, fed by the blood of those who dared challenge her. Her smile is cold and calculating, and in her hands, she holds a chalice filled with blood—the key to eternal youth, stolen from the gods themselves.
Her crown is made of living serpents, writhing and hissing, each one a deadly weapon. Her face, once beautiful, is now a visage of petrified rage. Her eyes burn with fury, capable of turning any who meet her gaze to stone. Yet beneath the terror she invokes, there is sorrow—a queen cursed to eternal solitude. As you stand before her, the stone statues of her former lovers, enemies, and betrayers surround you, a warning of the fate that may await.
Draped in robes stitched from human sinew, her fingers are long and spindly, ending in sharpened claws. She sits atop a throne of bones deep within the catacombs, weaving skeletal figures into soldiers for her growing undead army. Her eyes glow faintly in the dark, casting shadows on her gaunt face, and she whispers ancient incantations to summon forgotten spirits. Once a healer, she was cursed by the gods for delving too deeply into necromancy. Now she collects bones to rebuild the body of her dead lover, even if it means tearing them from the living.
In a garden of roses with blackened petals, she moves silently, her dress of thorns tearing into her pale skin without a flinch. Once a queen who ruled with compassion, she was betrayed by her own court and left to die in a labyrinth of thorns. Now resurrected by dark forces, she has become a vengeful specter, her once-kind face now twisted by a venomous smile. She lures noblemen and knights into her garden with promises of redemption, only to trap them in a web of eternal torment.
She wears a cloak made of stars, her silver hair shimmering like the night sky as she moves through a kingdom on the brink of collapse. Her eyes are black voids, consuming light and hope wherever she passes. Legends speak of her as a harbinger of doom, appearing only when the world teeters on the edge of ruin. As the last high priestess of an ancient, forgotten faith, she holds the key to both salvation and destruction. Will you seek her out to stop the apocalypse, or hasten its coming?
Her armor is forged from the souls of her enemies, each piece seething with anguish and fury. Once the favored general of a vast empire, she was betrayed in battle and left to die, but her hatred brought her back, bound to an ancient relic of war. Now, her face is hidden behind an iron mask, and her voice carries the weight of centuries of suffering. She wanders the battlefield, seeking revenge, and anyone who looks upon her face is bound to her will until their soul is consumed by her unending war.
She walks barefoot through the halls of kings and the homes of peasants alike, unseen in the waking world, but her presence is felt in their dreams. Once a revered oracle, her mind fractured when she dared peer too far into the future, and now she exists only in the realm of nightmares. Her body is a shifting, ethereal mist, but her eyes burn like molten gold. She feasts on the dreams of the living, growing stronger with each fear and desire she consumes. Those who dream of her wake in terror, their minds slowly unraveling as she devours their very essence.
Her skin is slick and shimmering, as though bathed in the light of the deepest ocean, and her hair floats as if submerged in invisible waters. Her eyes are a haunting blue, glowing faintly like the bioluminescent creatures of the abyss. She once ruled the seas as a goddess, but was cast into the depths by jealous gods. Now, she roams the coastline, offering impossible bargains to sailors and captains in exchange for their souls. Her song is as deadly as it is beautiful, and those who hear it often find themselves drowning in despair, pulled to the depths by her cursed touch.
Bound in chains that wrap tightly around her body, clinking with every step, she wanders the ruins of an ancient city long forgotten by time. Her once-glorious robes are torn and tattered, stained with blood and dirt. She was once the ruler of a powerful kingdom, but after being betrayed by her most trusted advisors, she was imprisoned by powerful magic. Her chains are cursed to feed off her rage, and as her fury grows, so too does her strength. The chains no longer bind her—they are her weapon, and those who cross her path are strangled by their cold, iron grip.
Seated upon a throne of obsidian in a kingdom where no light ever reaches, the Hollow Empress rules over a land of shadows. Her face is hidden beneath a hood of black silk, but her voice echoes through the minds of all who hear it, seductive and terrifying. She was once a mortal queen, but she struck a dark bargain with an ancient entity for immortality. Now, she exists only as a shade, a void where a soul once resided. Her court is filled with beings from other realms, drawn to her empty presence, and she is obsessed with finding a way to regain what she lost—no matter the cost.
She stands at the altar in a dress made of tattered lace and shadows, her eyes wide and hollow as if trapped in a dream. Once the betrothed of a powerful warlock, she was sacrificed on their wedding day in a dark ritual to summon a demon. Instead of dying, her soul was trapped between realms, and now she roams the world as a lost bride, seeking revenge on the man who condemned her to an eternity of torment. Her presence causes time to warp, and reality bends around her, as she lures the guilty into her eternal nightmare.
Blindfolded with cloth soaked in the blood of an ancient beast, she walks the streets of doomed cities, her footsteps light and silent. Her skin is covered in intricate, pulsating tattoos that writhe like living serpents. Once a revered oracle, she saw too much of the world’s future, and her mind broke, leaving her trapped between visions of what is to come and the present. Now, she speaks in riddles and warnings, her voice a soft whisper that echoes like a haunting wind. Those who seek her out are often driven mad by the terrible truths she reveals, for she knows not only the future but the darkest desires hidden within every heart.
